??　    調用「那裡有愛」

1 Every victory and obedience
Is so precious to Him.
Every victory and obedience
He so appreciates.

2 Faith on, darling; faith on, darling;
I am gazing on you.
Faith on, darling; faith on, darling;
Your victory I long for.

3 Faith on, darling; Faith on, darling;
I hold you with My hand.
Faith on, darling; faith on, darling;
I am looking on now.

4 Faith on, darling; faith on, darling;
You are spotless and pure.
Faith on, darling; faith on, darling;
You are so beautiful.

1 無論心被刺多少，主所受更多；
無論苦滋味如何，主所嘗更多。
心刺碎，豈怕再碎;
苦受透，豈懼再受。

2 雖然淚灑下如泉，主知道一切;
雖然汗流出成河，主記念一切。
淚擦乾，成人安慰;
汗抹淨，成主同工。

1. Tis so sweet to trust in Jesus
Just to take Him at His word;
Just to rest up on His pro-mise;
Just to know, Thus saith the Lord

Give me oil in my lamp to keep me burning;
Give me oil in my lamp, I pray;
Give me oil in my lamp to keep me burning;
Keep me burning till the break of day.
Sing Hosanna, Sing Hosanna,
Sing Hosanna to the King of kings!
Sing Hosanna, Sing Hosanna,
Sing Hosanna to the King!

Thy word is a lamp to my feet and a light to my path. 
Great peace have those who love Thy law; 
Nothing can make them stumble. (2)

When I am down and, oh my soul, so weary;
When troubles come and my heart burdened be;
Then, I am still and wait here in the silence,
Until you come and sit awhile with me.

You raise me up, so I can stand on mountains;
You raise me up, to walk on stormy seas;
I am strong, when I am on your shoulders;
You raise me up... To more than I can be.

You raise me up, so I can stand on mountains;
You raise me up, to walk on stormy seas;
I am strong, when I am on your shoulders;
You raise me up... To more than I can be.

There is no life - no life without its hunger;
Each restless heart beats so imperfectly;
But when you come and I am filled with wonder,
Sometimes, I think I glimpse eternity.

