You raise me up... To more than I can be.

Where Love Abides
1. Where love abides, where love abides, Mountains are turned to plains; Where love abides, where love abides, Darkness is turned to day.
2. Where love abides, where love abides, Winter feels just like spring;
Where love abides, where love abides, Sweetness whelms over pain.
3. Love your household, love your household, And you will see them change;
Don’t cease to pray, don’t cease to pray, And you’ll see God’s glory.

